				</div>
			
				<div class="comment-text">
					
					<p>Hi Amanda, the &#8220;Sleeping&#8221; Furby is apparently a problem a lot of people are having. Hasbro needs to do something about that for sure!   Try refreshing your Furby (It&#8217;s kind of like a Furby reboot).  To do that Remove the base of your Furby where the batteries go and push the refresh switch for 2 seconds, then replace the base.  If that doesn&#8217;t work you should look into exchanging it for another one where you purchased it.  If you bought it on eBay you have buyers protection, so just write the seller and let them know it does not work.  You can also try calling Hasbro Customer service at: 1-800-327-8264 or in the UK the number is: 00800 22 42 72 76.</p>

				</div>
			
			</div>
			
		</div>

